    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Arc and Endophilin Associate with Endosomes in Neurons\"\n- \"When co-expressed, Arc and endophilin 3 co-localized in puncta along the length of dendrites (Figure 5A). Thus, Arc redistributes to endophilin puncta in neurons. In addition, internalized GluR1 co-localized with endophilin 3 puncta (Figure 5B), suggesting that these puncta are receptor trafficking vesicles. Arc-endophilin vesicles also co-localized with endocytosed transferrin (Figure 5C), further suggesting that these are trafficking endosomes.\". Experimental description: - Species of neurons not stated in the paper, but traced back to PMID:861729: \"Rat hippocampal neurons in dispersed cell culture\"",
